main event: During the dates 3 February - 21 February 1956, sightings of unidentified flying objects were observed visually and in three instances by radar oscilloscope, operated by the 6702 AAA-AW BATTALION, at Camp Irwin, California. Witnesses reported sightings of oval-shaped, brilliant luminous objects and objects moving at extremely high speeds and altitudes.
interesting points: Multiple sightings of unidentified flying objects were reported visually and confirmed by radar detection at Camp Irwin, California.
Witnesses observed objects moving at estimated speeds of over 1,000 mph and at altitudes of 15,000 to 30,000 feet.
The objects were described as oval in shape, circular, metallic in construction, and with brilliant luminosity.
The sightings were reported by military personnel and confirmed by Air Force Intelligence, indicating credible witnesses.
Despite the lack of conclusive data, the objects were not definitively identified, and the case is carried as insufficient.
sighted object: unidentified flying objects, including oval-shaped and circular metallic objects
witnesses: military personnel, including PFC Richard L. Walker, PFC Richard E. Bolten, PFC Kenneth D. Marra, and others
